          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Collectively Achieving Recovery and Employment Act of 2018 or the CARE Act</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Labor, in collaboration with the Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration of the Department of Health and Human Services, to establish a pilot program to award grants during FY2019-FY2024 to counties (or other equivalent entities) and tribal entities to administer combined workforce training and drug addiction treatment and recovery programs.</p>]]></text>
